---
title: Sweet Heat Maple Sriracha Pork Chops with Chili-Roasted Carrots & Brussels Sprouts
description: Sweet and buttery with a touch of heat, our quick and delicious maple-Sriracha sauce elevates juicy pork chops to the next level. Sides of tender roasted carrots seasoned with Korean chili flakes and savory sautéed Brussels sprouts round out this plate that’s sure to tantalize your taste buds for a speedy weeknight dinner.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6643616a38584bf020f8c690-dab189de.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6643616a38584bf020f8c690-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 36 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 830 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-heat-maple-sriracha-pork-chops-6643616a38584bf020f8c690
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces (halve any larger carrots lengthwise first).

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}, @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (use less if you prefer less heat), and @salt{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}, @maple syrup{2%tablespoon}, @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}, and @water{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

Pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @shredded Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add Sriracha mixture; cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} (if sauce seems too thick, stir in water 1 tsp at a time).

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, carrots, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Spoon sauce over pork and serve.